a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.0346a3fb-df0b-4d04-91c9-fefc75adca04.description=Creates a target in Server Automation's Deployment Automation. The purpose of a target is to define the set of machines to which an application will be deployed. Inputs\: saHost - the host running DA that you want to connect to username - user name to use when connecting to DA password - the password to use when connecting to DA admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. appTierServerMapping - pipe "|" separated list of comma "," separated values of application tier and mapping target server. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.3ef8fd59-4010-460b-8a10-38f2c2792f73.prompt=Process Instance ID a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.3f6fd6d9-0f62-4b84-a174-0da8b6f9e2fa.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.433ebede-c2cc-4d04-8306-b02e6e39a972.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.52ad0744-c5c0-4d15-800e-6d26d4c01ae8.prompt=Process Instance ID a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.57776a69-f2b5-47aa-baa2-05c9ed3ee658.description=This operation deploys the given Application's Version on the required target. It will return the details of DeploymentJob created for deploying the version. This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later. Inputs\: coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443' coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS' coreUsername - Username of the SA. corePassword - Password of SA user. coreVersion - [Optional] By default, it is the SA version being used. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. isAdmUndeployPreVersion - [Optional] Should the ADM undeploy the previous version of application? (y/n) By default it is 'y' timeout - [Optional] Job timeout in millisecond, If it is zero (0) then the given operation will return immediately. By default it is '20000' admJobComment - [Optional] Job Comment. Outputs\: status - Operation completion Status. idAdmDeploymentJob - ADM Id of Application Deployment job. admJobStatus - Status of Job. It could be one of [NOT_STARTED, CANCEL_PENDING, CANCELED, PAUSE_PENDING, PAUSED, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED, FAILED, ATTENTION_REQUIRED]. admJobComment - Job Comment. isAdmJobRollbacked - Is rollbacked? (y/n). isAdmJobUndeployed - Is Undeployed? (y/n) idAdmRollbackedJob - ADM id of Rollback Job. idAdmUndeployedJob - ADM id of Undeployed Job. admJobStagedDate - Application staged date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). Is available only for SA 9. admJobDeployedDate - Application deployed date. (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH\:mm\:ss.SSSZ). admJobType - Type of Job. It could be one of [DEPLOYMENT, MAKE_VERSION, ROLLBACK, UNDEPLOYMENT]. idSaJob - SA Id Of SA Job. idAdmVersion - ADM Id of Application Version. admVersion - ADM Name of ADM Application Version. idAdmRelease - ADM Id of Application Release. admRelease - ADM Name of ADM Application Release. idAdmApplication - ADM Id of Application. admApplication - ADM Name of ADM Application. idAdmTarget - ADM Id of Application Target. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. idAdmEnvironment - ADM Id of Application Environment. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. Responses\: success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'. failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'. a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.6b2741df-df6c-4a1a-a7f4-4bcbfd66f1d2.prompt=User Identifier a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.7093c1fd-1a09-4ba1-a2f2-25bbe8fb7ff3.description=This workflow returns the artifact's properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.76c21cc5-4047-419d-ad56-0e46670fa0ff.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application. a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.771a4b4c-aa99-4d50-8691-40c5a7bc1676.prompt=Username of the SA. a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.7f7b76ee-001e-42b5-a2c6-22ef8fce295d.prompt=User Identifier a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.8eb22c20-5ced-40f1-a88e-2c52013d350a.description=This workflow returns the artifact's properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.902478ea-4670-426c-9ea4-eaf09396ab45.prompt=User Identifier a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.a339b9a0-366a-4812-be8a-9ae45ebea104.prompt=Password of SA user. a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.a7ee2a3d-8b14-4425-8748-693d6bf1f427.prompt=Resource Provider ID a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.aedc2d55-6290-4bdc-8c4d-1626bc6069ee.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

Results\: providerSAP providerUsername providerPassword a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.cf2c684a-b5a5-46f1-be6a-1555ff3c9f16.prompt=Process Instance ID a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.d6eb73c3-107c-49f4-98b9-0c3c9e8258a6.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.d93d96fe-f0fd-4b4d-ab4f-0ed63dd13c46.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API. Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State a3d3f09f-8eb8-43f5-a539-dc5b4d8affe0.description=
Provision a server, add them into the tier and deploy application

Inputs Parameters\:

 CSA_CONTEXT_ID – CSA Context Id
 CSA_PROCESS_ID – CSA Process Instance Id
 SVC_COMPONENT_ID - This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
 RSC_PROVIDER_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL - This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
 RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time.
  		Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE - This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
 RSC_POOL_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
 SVC_INSTANCE_ID - This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
 SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID - This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
 PRN_COMPONENT_ID – This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
 REQ_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
 REQ_USER_ID - This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
 USR_ORG_ID - This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
 RSC_BINDING_ID - This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.
